---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Web Design for Electricians | FisherDigital"
  description="Websites built for electrical contractors across the UK. Show up when homeowners search, display your certifications, and book more rewires, fuseboard upgrades, and testing work."
  schemaType="niche"
  niche="Electricians"
  nicheDescription="Professional websites, AI chatbots, and smart automations designed for electricians and electrical contractors in the UK."
>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="section-light py-(--spacing-section)">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <span class="label block mb-4">Web design for electricians</span>
        <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-heading font-600 tracking-tight mb-6">
          Certified work deserves<br />
          <span class="text-accent">a certified website.</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-[var(--color-light-text-secondary)] max-w-xl mb-10 leading-relaxed">
          Homeowners Google "electrician near me" and pick from the first three results. If your NICEIC badge, five-star reviews, and service list aren't visible in seconds, you've already lost the job. We fix that.
        </p>
        <a href="/#contact" data-hover
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 bg-accent text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-full text-sm font-600 hover:bg-accent-hover transition-all shadow-lg shadow-accent/20 hover:shadow-accent/40">
          Book a free call
          <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 8l4 4m0 0l-4 4m4-4H3"/></svg>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pain Points -->
  <section class="bg-white py-(--spacing-section)">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <span class="label block mb-4">The problem</span>
        <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-heading font-600 tracking-tight">
          Good sparks, bad marketing.
        </h2>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 max-w-5xl mx-auto">
        <!-- Pain 1 -->
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-[var(--color-border)] p-8 bg-[var(--color-surface-light)]">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-accent/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-5">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-accent" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m5.618-4.016A11.955 11.955 0 0112 2.944a11.955 11.955 0 01-8.618 3.04A12.02 12.02 0 003 9c0 5.591 3.824 10.29 9 11.622 5.176-1.332 9-6.03 9-11.622 0-1.042-.133-2.052-.382-3.016z"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-heading font-600 mb-3">Certifications buried or missing</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
            You've got NICEIC, Part P, 18th Edition. But if your website doesn't show them front and centre, customers have no reason to trust you over a random handyman on Facebook.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Pain 2 -->
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-[var(--color-border)] p-8 bg-[var(--color-surface-light)]">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-accent/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-5">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-accent" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M19 11H5m14 0a2 2 0 012 2v6a2 2 0 01-2 2H5a2 2 0 01-2-2v-6a2 2 0 012-2m14 0V9a2 2 0 00-2-2M5 11V9a2 2 0 012-2m0 0V5a2 2 0 012-2h6a2 2 0 012 2v2M7 7h10"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-heading font-600 mb-3">No clear list of services</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
            Rewires, fuseboard upgrades, EICRs, EV charger installs, commercial fit-outs. You do all of it. But your website just says "electrical services." That doesn't rank on Google and doesn't tell customers what you actually offer.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Pain 3 -->
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-[var(--color-border)] p-8 bg-[var(--color-surface-light)]">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-accent/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-5">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-accent" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M17.657 18.657A8 8 0 016.343 7.343S7 9 9 10c0-2 .5-5 2.986-7C14 5 16.09 5.777 17.656 7.343A7.975 7.975 0 0120 13a7.975 7.975 0 01-2.343 5.657z"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-heading font-600 mb-3">Relying on word of mouth alone</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
            Referrals are great until they dry up. When work slows down, you need customers finding you online. Without a proper web presence, you're invisible to anyone outside your existing network.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What We Build -->
  <section class="section-light py-(--spacing-section)">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <span class="label block mb-4">What you get</span>
        <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-heading font-600 tracking-tight mb-12">
          Built for how electricians actually work.
        </h2>

        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-accent mt-1 shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
            <div>
              <p class="font-600 text-[var(--color-light-text)] mb-1">Certification badges displayed prominently</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-light-text-secondary)]">NICEIC, NAPIT, Part P, 18th Edition. Visible on every page, not hidden in a footer link. Trust signals that make customers choose you over uncertified competitors.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-accent mt-1 shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
            <div>
              <p class="font-600 text-[var(--color-light-text)] mb-1">Dedicated pages for every service</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-light-text-secondary)]">One page per service: rewires, fuseboards, testing, EV chargers, smart home installs. Each page targets what real customers actually search for in your area.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-accent mt-1 shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
            <div>
              <p class="font-600 text-[var(--color-light-text)] mb-1">Photo gallery of completed work</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-light-text-secondary)]">Before and after shots of consumer units, neat wiring runs, and finished installs. Real photos build more trust than any amount of sales copy.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-accent mt-1 shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
            <div>
              <p class="font-600 text-[var(--color-light-text)] mb-1">Quote request form that qualifies the job</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-light-text-secondary)]">Not a generic contact form. Ours asks what type of work, the property type, and preferred dates. You get useful information before you even ring them back.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="bg-white py-(--spacing-section)">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-heading font-600 tracking-tight mb-6">
        Ready to get found online?
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] max-w-xl mx-auto mb-10">
        We'll show you exactly what we'd build for your business. Free call, no pressure, no jargon.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-center gap-5">
        <a href="/#portfolio" data-hover
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 bg-accent text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-full text-sm font-600 hover:bg-accent-hover transition-all shadow-lg shadow-accent/20 hover:shadow-accent/40">
          See our work
          <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M10 6H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2h10a2 2 0 002-2v-4M14 4h6m0 0v6m0-6L10 14"/></svg>
        </a>
        <a href="/#contact" data-hover
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] px-8 py-4 rounded-full text-sm font-500 border border-[var(--color-border-light)] hover:border-accent hover:text-accent transition-all">
          Book a free call
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
